    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Architectural style that references the Spanish Renaissance, Spanish Colonial, Italian Renaissance, Venetian Gothic, French Colonial, Beaux-Arts, and Arabic Andalusian architecture. It focused heavily on the style of palaces and villas. It flourished in the United States from 1890s through 1930s.</Note_Text>
